If you play one of our games, we will always access data from and / or store data on the device that you are using. This data is necessary to deliver our games, and includes:
•   Content Data: Game content data, such as video, audio, graphic, text, and game level information that is requested and downloaded for the game that you are accessing online. If you are playing an online game, this includes your online interactions as necessary to reflect those interactions on our game servers.
•   Account Data: Information required to sign you into your account for PlayStation™Network. 
•   Configuration Data: Information about the configuration of your device and the game you are playing , such as the device date, time and language settings and your in-game preference and settings. 
•   Security Data: Information necessary to detect and investigate malicious, unauthorized or fraudulent activity.
•   Legal Data: Information required by applicable law and to demonstrate compliance.
If you agree, we may collect more detailed information about how you interact with our games.
This may include when and how you use the game’s user interface, which parts of the game you visit, which weapons you use, which characters you interact with and any errors that you encounter.
Game Data is usually sent to us and stored with one or more unique network, device and/or account identifiers.

Freedom has come under a two-sided attack. In an act of sinister syncronicity, both the Terminids and Automatons have launched large-scale assaults.

Intel suggests the Automatons are capitalising on our brief redirection to the Terminid front. This was to be anticipated, and is likely their final attempt to push past our defences. We must outlast their aggression.

The simultaneous Terminid attack, by contrast, was unexpected. While some behavioural experts posit that it could be an instinctual response to our recent E-710 procurement efforts, we cannot rule out the possibility of bug-robot collusion.

The stakes are high. The Automatons threaten to use overwhelming force to break through the Menkent Line, leaving us vulnerable to severe losses. The Terminids threaten the construction of nascent E-710 farms, jeopardising our energy security and depriving deserving citizens of their jobs.

The Helldivers must defend our citizens on both fronts at once.

What screams "Presidential"? Why, the Tactical Warhead booster, of course!

Normally reserved for only the most elite officers and politicians, now, thanks to the President's Football booster pack, you, too, have the opportunity to unleash total liberty with a well-aimed tactical warhead! Simply spend a few supercreds, then make the call, and the enemies of liberty will be no more.

But that's not all. This booster pack also includes the S.E.A.F. Troop Support booster. That's right, call in the reserves at a moment's notice. Now that is democracy.

Achieve your untapped potential with the Muscle-Enhancing Steroids booster, allowing you to traverse terrain faster and hit enemies harder. Plus, with a backup crew set to deploy at a moment's notice, you'll be even more free to rush headfirst into whatever situation the enemies of liberty may throw at you.

Limitless Reserves: because no mission is ever lost.

Booster Pack Includes:
Backup Crew Booster (2)
Muscle-Enhancing Steroid Booster (4)
The Knowledge that your Objectives will be Completed, Somehow
An Unquestionable Sense of Self *DUT
